doc.previous: The Teledyne CAE J69 was a small turbojet engine originally produced by Continental Aviation and Engineering CAE under license from Turbomeca A development of the Turbomeca Marbor II the J69 powered a number of US drones missiles and small aircraft Later produced by Teledyne CAE the J69 was also developed into the Teledyne CAE J100 turbojet optimized for higher altitudes
